fr.apteryx.imageio.dicom
Class StorageCommitmentSCP

Object
  StorageCommitmentSCP

public class StorageCommitmentSCP
extends Object

Implements a Storage Commitment SCP. A Storage Commitment SCP is used to receive requests from a SCU to safekeep SOP instances that has previously been received (typically using the Storage Service Class).

If a listener is specified in a constructor, the listener method is called when a request is received. If no listener is specified, the user must call receiveRequest, which blocks until a request is received.

Calling receiveRequest when a listener was specified in a constructor may lead to unexpected results.

The content of the request is described by a StorageCommitmentSCP.Request instance. Its commit() or cannotCommit() method must be called for each SOP instance referenced in the request. When the request has been fully processed, its sendResult() method must be called to send the information to the SCU. These calls may occur either from the requestReceived listener, or from a different thread. The result will be sent to the SCU using the same association that it receives the request from, if such association is still alive, or will try to establish a new association with the SCU. To be able to establish such association, the AE title the SCU used when sending the request must be registered in the AERegistry of the server.

StorageCommitmentSCP

public StorageCommitmentSCP(int port,
                            InetAddress addr,
                            SecureTransport st)
Creates a Storage Commitment SCP that will listen for Storage Commitment Requests on the specified port and address when start() is called. Transport will be insecure if st is null. The SCP will listen to all local addresses if addr is null. receiveRequest must me called for receiving requests.

StorageCommitmentSCP

public StorageCommitmentSCP(int port,
                            InetAddress addr,
                            SecureTransport st,
                            StorageCommitmentRequestListener listener)
Creates a Storage Commitment SCP that will listen for Storage Commitment Requests on the specified port and address when start() is called. The requestReceived method of the specified StorageCommitmentRequestListener will be called when a request is received. Transport will be insecure if st is null. The SCP will listen to all local addresses if addr is null.

receiveRequest

public StorageCommitmentSCP.Request receiveRequest()
                                            throws InterruptedException
Blocks until a request is received. This method must be called only if a listener was not specified in the constructor. A response with a "success" status is automatically sent to the SCU when a request is received. To control the response sent to the request, a Storage Commitment SCP instantiated with listener must be used instead.

Throws:
InterruptedException

setApplicationTitles

public void setApplicationTitles(String[] calling,
                                 String[] called)
This class will only handle messages from associations using calling and called Application Entitities (AE) titles listed in the specified arrays. Passing a null array means that any AE will be accepted. By default, every called and calling AE are accepted. This method must be called before the service is started.

setApplicationTitles

public void setApplicationTitles(String calling,
                                 String called)
Convenient replacement for setApplicationTitles(String[], String[]) when using single titles. Passing a null String meants that any AE will be accepted.
